Contact Person: Catherine Mills

Latino Materials: Newspapers, Letters and/or correspondence, Photographs, Artifacts, Books, Pamphlets, Audio Visual, Manuscripts

Details: Biographical clippings mostly from the San José Mercury News and scattered clippings from earlier San José newspapers; Obituaries Index 1879 to 1912. Index lists date of obituary and newspaper. Newspapers indexed include the (San José) Daily Morning Times, San José Evening News, San José Daily News, San José (Daily) Herald, and the San José Mercury; On microfilm: Daily Morning Times, July 1879 – December 1881; July-December 1884; Morning Times, October 1906 – September 1909; San José Daily City Item, February 1884 – March 1885; San José Herald, September 1876 – December 1889; July 1890 – December 1896; July 1897 – December 1900; San José Mercury, November 1861 December 1862; August 1869 – January 1870; San José Daily News, March 1885 – December 1886; San José Evening News, January 1887 – December 1896; July 1897 –December 1936; March 1937 – December 1947.

Name: <center><font size="5">San Juan Capistrano Historical Society</center></font>
Description:
Website: http://sjchistoricalsociety.com/contact/

Type of Organization: Musuem

Address: 31831 Los Rios Street San Juan Capistrano, CA 92675

Phone: (949) 493-8444

Contact Email: museum@capistranohistory.org

Contact Person: Jan Siegel

Latino Materials: Newspapers, Photographs, Artifacts, Books, Pamphlets, Newsletters, Audio Visual, Manuscripts, structures

Details: Mission town founded by St. Junipero Serra, 7th in California Mission chain. They have thousands of photographs and hundreds of artifacts, books, pamphlets, etc. Their location is on the oldest residential street in California. On the street is the oldest house in California with the same family living in it. The current owner's children are 10th generation living in that house. They are Hispanic. They are currently preserving an adobe house from 1840 on our property, built by an Hispanic and they will use it to highlight our artifacts of that period which was the Mexican period in California. Hispanic culture is the core of the community. Spanish, Mexican, Basque have all played an integral part of their history.
Location:
31831 Los Rios Street
 San Juan Capistrano, CA 92675
